</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFDF7F8EEFD7DF8C4" box="[554,752,1885,1909]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFDF7F8EEFD11F8C4" box="[554,668,1885,1909]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFAABA6AFF6EF8CEFE8AF824" box="[179,263,1917,1941]" name="Taiwan" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFAABA6AFECBF8CEFE19F824" box="[278,404,1917,1941]" name="Philippines" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, and Sulawesi and commented on the problems with the two genera. They showed that 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFD04F82DFE8CF864" baseAuthorityName="Rathbun" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippinense">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFD04F82DFE8CF864" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. philippinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFDACF80DFD65F864" baseAuthorityName="De Man" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[625,744,1981,2005]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipes">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFDACF80DFD65F864" box="[625,744,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. brevipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; recognised a new species, 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFE45F86DFDA9F844" authorityName="Li, Shih &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2019" box="[408,548,2013,2037]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eurypleon">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFE45F86DFDA9F844" box="[408,548,2013,2037]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. eurypleon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a diagnostic G1 structure with an elongate distal chitinous part; described a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFC25FF0DFBE2FF64" authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[1016,1135,190,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFC25FF0DFBE2FF64" box="[1016,1135,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFB59FF0DFB50FF64" authorityName="Li, Shih &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2020" box="[1156,1245,190,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mora">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFB59FF0DFB50FF64" box="[1156,1245,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">S. mora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and redescribed 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFCF0FF6DFBC4FF44" baseAuthorityName="Rathbun" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[813,1097,221,245]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" sensu="stricto" species="mindanaoensis">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFCF0FF6DFBC4FF44" box="[813,1097,221,245]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E8FBFB29FFAABA6AFB8CFF6DFB00FF44" box="[1105,1165,222,245]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFAABA6AFCF0FEAEFC51FD04" blockId="75.[813,1452,285,693]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFAABA6AFCF0FEAEFBA1FE84" author="Serene R &amp; Soh CL" box="[813,1068,285,309]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="387 - 416" refId="ref76461" refString="Serene R &amp; Soh CL (1970) New IndoPacific genera allied to Sesarma Say 1877 (Brachyura, Decapoda, Crustacea). Treubia, 27: 387 - 416." type="journal article" year="1970">Serène &amp; Soh (1970)</bibRefCitation>
noted that both 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFB26FEADFAFAFE84" authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[1275,1399,286,309]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFB26FEADFAFAFE84" box="[1275,1399,286,309]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFCF0FE8EFC12FEE4" authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[813,927,317,341]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFCF0FE8EFC12FEE4" box="[813,927,317,341]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were related in having the male telson sunken into the distal margin of somite 6. They separated 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFAE5FEEDFA26FEC4" authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[1336,1451,350,373]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFAE5FEEDFA26FEC4" box="[1336,1451,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as having a more trapezoidal carapace versus a rectangular carapace for 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFC1DFE2EFBB9FE04" authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[960,1076,413,437]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFC1DFE2EFBB9FE04" box="[960,1076,413,437]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Ongoing studies now show that neither the carapace shape, nor the male telson are reliable characters at the generic level. Both genera are very close, and some species now placed in these genera do not possess the distinctive telson-somite 6 feature. There are also several kinds of G1 structures present, and it is clear that a full revision of both genera will be needed. This is beyond the scope of the present paper and will have to be undertaken at a future time.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C1039A40FFAABA6AFCF0FD6DFAB1FB04" blockId="75.[813,1452,733,1206]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">
For the present work, only one species is treated as it had been placed in 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFBD1FD4EFB3BFCA4" authorityName=", Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[1036,1206,765,789]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Pseudosesarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFBD1FD4EFB3BFCA4" box="[1036,1206,765,789]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Pseudosesarma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
previously— 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFA93FD4DFB6CFC84" authority="Zehntner, 1894" authorityName="Zehntner" authorityYear="1894" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="edwardsi" variety="laevimana">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFA93FD4DFC02FC84" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarma edwardsi</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFC1AFCAEFBBBFC84" box="[967,1078,797,821]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">laevimana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFAABA6AFBE3FCAEFB6CFC84" author="Zehntner L" box="[1086,1249,797,821]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="135 - 214" refId="ref78899" refString="Zehntner L (1894) Crustaces de l'Archipel Malais. Voyage de MM. M. Bedot et C. Pictet dans l'Archipel Malais. Revue Suisse de Zoologie et Annales du Musee d'Histoire Naturelle de Geneve, 2: 135 - 214, pls. 7 - 9." type="journal article" year="1894">Zehntner, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
—and we find that it is actually a senior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFAEBFC8EFBDEFCC4" authority="(Tweedie, 1940)" baseAuthorityName="Tweedie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sediliense">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFAEBFC8EFC1BFCC4" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium sediliense</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A52DE7B1FFAABA6AFC78FCEEFBC6FCC4" author="Tweedie MWF" box="[933,1099,861,885]" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" pagination="88 - 113" refId="ref78385" refString="Tweedie MWF (1940) New and interesting Malaysian species of Sesarma and Utica (Crustacea, Brachyura). Bulletin of the Raffles Museum, 16: 88 - 113, figs. 1 - 12, pl. 24." type="journal article" year="1940">Tweedie, 1940</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Specimens from Lorentz River in New 
<collectingCountry id="B9ABDAD0FFAABA6AFC57FCCEFC54FC24" box="[906,985,893,917]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Guinea</collectingCountry>
which have been identified as “ 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFA90FCCDFC11FC04" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevimana">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFA90FCCDFC11FC04" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarma laevimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in NMBA are here identified as a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFC91FC0DFC4EFC64" authorityName="Schubart &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2020" box="[844,963,958,981]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Migmarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFC91FC0DFC4EFC64" box="[844,963,958,981]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Migmarma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFC0FFC0DFBC5FC64" authorityName="Schubart &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2020" box="[978,1096,957,981]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Migmarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lorentzi">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFC0FFC0DFBC5FC64" box="[978,1096,957,981]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">M. lorentzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see later). The placement of 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFA49FC0DFC15FC44" baseAuthorityName="Tweedie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sediliense">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFA49FC0DFC15FC44" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. sediliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFC1CFC6EFBB9FC44" authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[961,1076,989,1013]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFC1CFC6EFBB9FC44" box="[961,1076,989,1013]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as presently diagnosed is mainly because of the male telson being prominently sunken into the distal margin of somite 6 and the G1 having the distal chitinous part elongate. In the phylogenetic tree (
<figureCitation id="598786C5FFAABA6AFA91FB8EFA12FBE4" box="[1356,1439,1085,1109]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="91.[113,149,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[116,1448,352,1737]" captionTargetId="figure-15@91.[86,1475,347,1749]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="Fig. 59. Phylogenetic relationships among selected taxa of Sesarmidae (91 OTUs), including all representatives of Chiromantes and Pseudosesarma previous to current revision of these genera. In addition, several species of Bresedium and Sesarmops are considered, as the revision also involves some of their former members. Topology and confidence values were determined by means of a phylogenetic reconstruction based on 1,096 basepairs of mtDNA (16S-tRNALeu-ND1), conducted with MrBayes, GTR+I+G as substitution model, and Parasesarma plicatum as outgroup (midpoint rooting). Posterior probabilities were determined after 4 million generations with a burn-in of 25%. All species so far classified within Chiromantes (without obvious anterolateral teeth) are shaded in blue, whereas those species that used to be classified in Pseudosesarma (carrying at least one pair of anterolateral teeth) are shaded in yellow." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351405/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFCF0FBEDFC39FBC4" baseAuthorityName="Tweedie" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[813,948,1117,1141]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sediliense">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFCF0FBEDFC39FBC4" box="[813,948,1117,1141]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">B. sediliense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not part of but adjacent to the main clade of 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFCF0FBCEFC12FB24" authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[813,927,1149,1173]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Bresedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFCF0FBCEFC12FB24" box="[813,927,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Bresedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="06BCE1C3FFAABA6AFC04FBCDFBC0FB24" authorityName="Serene &amp; Soh" authorityYear="1970" box="[985,1101,1150,1173]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="75" pageNumber="966" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F3C84652FFAABA6AFC04FBCDFBC0FB24" box="[985,1101,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="966">Sesarmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although the bootstrap support is not considered strong enough to be definitive.
</paragraph>
